title: Australian Federal Police member taken to hospital after ‘shooting incident’ at Melbourne headquarters - 9news.com.au
text:
Australian Federal Police member taken to hospital after ‘shooting incident’ at Melbourne headquarters By 9NEWS An ambulance attends the La Trobe Street headquarters. (9NEWS) 
An Australian Federal Police member has been taken to hospital after a shooting incident at the AFP headquarters in Melbourne. 
The AFP confirmed police and ambulance responded to the shooting at the La Trobe Street headquarters this afternoon, after a person received a gunshot wound while inside the building about 5.45pm. 
Police are not looking for anyone else in connection to the shooting. © Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
